  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Modelling Mississippi River</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Major rivers Such the river Rhine and the  Mississippi are crucial for the population in the river basins. To optimizing use of the rivers many interventions took place. Some of these have negative impact on the river system. Upstream dams can result in erosion of delta&#x2019;s that can not cope the sea level rise. Agricultural practice along the river can result in too high levels of nutrients causing algae or fish mortality downstream.PBL launched a website &#x2018;Navigating Rivers and Deltas towards a Sustainable Future&#x2019;. This website is a tool for governments, investors, and all relevant stakeholders to assist in making the choices that allows for sustainable river management and planning in river basins.In the PvW programme with the USA PBL will model the Mississippi in line with the principles mentioned above. In this specific project the following activities will be executed:In cooperation with experts from the USA the most relevant stress elements will be identified. These stress factors, the effects they have and possible solutions will be described and substantiated with relevant scientific literature. The texts will be verified and discussed with experts from the USA. Infographics are made to visualize the possible solutions on the website.</narrative>
  </description>
